## Component Development

### Creating New Components

1. **HTML Structure** - Use semantic HTML
2. **Apply Foundation Classes** - Style with utility classes
3. **Component CSS** (if needed) - Only for component-specific behavior
4. **Follow BEM** - Use `.component__element--modifier` pattern

### Example Component Pattern
```html
<!-- Card component using foundation classes -->
<div class="card card--with-border p-24 mb-16">
  <h2 class="card__heading text-lg font-semibold mb-12">Card Title</h2>
  <div class="card__content text-md">
    <p class="mb-8">Card content here</p>
  </div>
</div>
```

---

## Theme System

SwageCSS supports multiple themes via `data-theme` attribute:

```html
<html data-theme="cui">  <!-- Default: Curative UI theme -->
<html data-theme="blv">  <!-- Alternate: BLV theme -->
```

Components automatically adapt to themes using CSS variables. Always use semantic variables (`--color-text-default`) instead of direct colors (`--color-blue-500`) for theme compatibility.

